# Swaps Feature Conventions

## Service Layer (`services/swaps_service.py`)

### Repository pattern

`SwapPricingService` owns two repositories:

| Class | Mode | Backend |
|-------|------|---------|
| `SwapLiveRepository` | live | MARS REST API via `MarsClient` |
| `SwapDemoRepository` | demo | JSON snapshots under `demo_data/` |

Always instantiate via `SwapPricingService.from_settings()`.

### `SwapQuery` fields

```python
@dataclass
class SwapQuery:
    deal_type:    str
    maturity_date: date   # not tenor string — user edits directly
    effective:    date
    notional:     float
    leg2_notional: float
    currency:     str
    solve_for:    str
    discount_curve_id:  str
    forward_curve_id:   str
    leg1_discount_id:   str
    collateral_currency: str
    csa_rate:     float
```

### Solvable fields

Fetch dynamically from `GET /marswebapi/v1/dealSchema?tail={deal_type}`.
Filter on `solvableTarget == true`. Fall back to `_DEMO_SOLVABLE[deal_type]` on failure.

```python
# ❌ BAD — hardcoded
solve_options = ["Coupon", "Spread"]
# ✅ GOOD — dynamic with demo fallback
solve_options = svc.fetch_solvable_fields(deal_type)
```

### Deal structure body

Use `"tail"` + `"dealStructureOverride"` — never `"structureRequest"`.

### Curve IDs

Always use `S{number}` format (e.g. `"S329"`). IDs must exist in `configs/curves_catalog.py`.

### Demo snapshots

Filenames follow `{currency}_{tenor}.json` (e.g. `COP_5Y.json`). Fall back to `_5Y.json` when not found.

